<td style="text-align:center">For cross-origin socket connections, use this property to choose a route to send an initial JSONP request (in browser environments) or HTTP request (in Node.js environments) in order to retrieve a cookie, so that a session can be established.  The route should return the string <code>_sailsIoJSConnect()</code>, which will allow the connection to continue.  If <code>useCORSRouteToGetCookie</code> is <code>true</code>, the default <code>/__getcookie</code> route on the Sails server will be used.  If it is <code>false</code>, no attempt will be made to contact the remote server before continuing the socket connection.</td>
